  "@type": "Article",
  "dateModified": "2026-03-03",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-03",
  "description": "Colonialism is the practice of one people establishing political control over another people\u0026rsquo;s territory, exploiting its resources and labor, and imposing its governance systems. When European powers seized territories across Africa, Asia, and the Americas, they didn\u0026rsquo;t just take land — they restructured entire societies. They imposed legal systems, religious institutions, languages, property regimes, and racial hierarchies designed to make extraction efficient and resistance difficult. Colonialism is not simply foreign rule; it is the reorganization of a society for the benefit of the colonizer.\n",
